61
00:03:56,916 --> 00:04:00,226
And the first one
is bad app icons.


62
00:04:00,226 --> 00:04:04,566
So this is the first place
that most people are going


63
00:04:04,566 --> 00:04:05,636
to encounter your app.


64
00:04:06,936 --> 00:04:09,116
They're going to search for
something and your app is going


65
00:04:09,116 --> 00:04:12,346
to come up in the results
alongside dozens and dozens


66
00:04:12,346 --> 00:04:15,386
of other apps, and you have
to standout from the crowd.


67
00:04:16,296 --> 00:04:17,536
This is a search for camera,


68
00:04:17,786 --> 00:04:19,125
I just did this couple
of weeks ago.


69
00:04:19,805 --> 00:04:22,156
And I bet there're some
icons here that are standing


70
00:04:22,156 --> 00:04:25,626
out better than others, that
you noticed first immediately,


71
00:04:25,676 --> 00:04:26,936
right when we got to the slide.


72
00:04:27,656 --> 00:04:29,586
And that's not unlike
what happens


73
00:04:29,586 --> 00:04:33,206
when you did the search yourself
at home on your computer.


74
00:04:34,066 --> 00:04:35,436
Things are going to
draw your eye in,


75
00:04:35,966 --> 00:04:40,416
and you immediately begin
to make a lot of assumptions


76
00:04:40,796 --> 00:04:44,556
about the user experience of
these apps, so you'll look


77
00:04:44,556 --> 00:04:46,906
at them and start to
make these inferences


78
00:04:46,906 --> 00:04:49,826
about how enjoyable
they're going to be to use,


79
00:04:49,966 --> 00:04:51,716
how intuitive the
interface is going to be,


80
00:04:52,276 --> 00:04:54,826
how well it's going
to serve your needs.


81
00:04:55,446 --> 00:04:56,546
And I think those are kind


82
00:04:56,546 --> 00:04:59,626
of reasonable assumptions
actually to make from an icon.


83
00:04:59,626 --> 00:05:01,556
I mean, if an icon looks great


84
00:05:01,556 --> 00:05:04,806
and it obviously was carefully
crafted, it's reasonable


85
00:05:04,806 --> 00:05:09,146
to assume that the rest of the
design of the app is also great


86
00:05:09,396 --> 00:05:10,636
and also well crafted.


87
00:05:11,166 --> 00:05:13,316
But it goes beyond that.


88
00:05:13,666 --> 00:05:14,866
People start to make all sorts


89
00:05:14,866 --> 00:05:16,576
of other assumptions
about your app.


90
00:05:18,016 --> 00:05:19,366
How good the technology is.


91
00:05:19,886 --> 00:05:21,426
How secure your data is.


92
00:05:21,906 --> 00:05:23,216
How performant it is.


93
00:05:23,506 --> 00:05:24,366
Is it stable?


94
00:05:25,346 --> 00:05:29,146
Is it going to have
functionality which is ahead--


95
00:05:29,266 --> 00:05:32,236
you know, advanced better
than the competition?


96
00:05:32,806 --> 00:05:35,356
So with that in mind,


97
00:05:35,576 --> 00:05:38,526
an app icon is really an
important thing to focus on.


98
00:05:39,986 --> 00:05:40,916
And what are the qualities


99
00:05:40,916 --> 00:05:43,536
that distinguish a
really great app icon?


100
00:05:44,076 --> 00:05:45,506
Well, there's two main things.


101
00:05:45,926 --> 00:05:50,326
One, it's beautiful and I think
probably more importantly,


102
00:05:50,326 --> 00:05:52,076
it's instantly recognizable.


103
00:05:52,666 --> 00:05:56,196
So how do you accomplish that?


104
00:05:56,656 --> 00:05:58,646
Well, there're six things
that I want to point


105
00:05:58,646 --> 00:06:00,696
out that are important
to keep in mind.


106
00:06:00,696 --> 00:06:04,196
I think they distinguish
every great app icon.


107
00:06:04,736 --> 00:06:09,336
The first, focus
on unique shape.


108
00:06:10,366 --> 00:06:12,746
These four icons, they
do different things,


109
00:06:12,746 --> 00:06:16,146
some are very simple
or with solid colors,


110
00:06:16,146 --> 00:06:17,326
or just a clean gradient.


111
00:06:17,666 --> 00:06:21,206
Others are a little bit more
complex but they all start


112
00:06:21,206 --> 00:06:24,106
with this very basic
shape, and that allows them


113
00:06:24,106 --> 00:06:26,776
to be recognizable
at a great distance.


114
00:06:27,666 --> 00:06:28,476
So you guys in the back


115
00:06:28,476 --> 00:06:31,216
of the room right now are
having a really easy time making


116
00:06:31,216 --> 00:06:35,386
out what the shape of these
icons is, and that's important.


117
00:06:35,996 --> 00:06:37,776
Icons are seen at
all different sizes.


118
00:06:37,776 --> 00:06:42,166
You know, it's not just the
size you see in the store,


119
00:06:42,336 --> 00:06:44,866
it gets smaller on the
home screen and smaller


120
00:06:44,866 --> 00:06:46,076
on the notification center


121
00:06:46,076 --> 00:06:47,536
and it's really small
inside the groups.


122
00:06:47,536 --> 00:06:50,196
So you have to make sure
that the imaging you choose


123
00:06:50,196 --> 00:06:52,366
for your app icon is kind
of reduce really well


124
00:06:52,786 --> 00:06:54,416
and be clear at any size.


125
00:06:56,616 --> 00:07:00,936
The next step is to just
choose a limited pallet,


126
00:07:02,116 --> 00:07:03,936
one color, maybe two.


127
00:07:04,846 --> 00:07:07,856
Now, there're app icons that
have much more than one color


128
00:07:07,856 --> 00:07:11,296
or two but it's really
complicated to pull off right.


129
00:07:11,956 --> 00:07:14,456
We'll see an example of it in
a few moments and I'll point it


130
00:07:14,456 --> 00:07:17,186
out when we get there,
but notice these icons,


131
00:07:18,196 --> 00:07:21,016
just really one color and
it has variations and tone


132
00:07:21,896 --> 00:07:24,766
but they stand out,
they're not fragmented.


133
00:07:25,346 --> 00:07:30,316
Now, the next one is to
avoid using photography


134
00:07:30,316 --> 00:07:31,246
in your app icon.


135
00:07:31,396 --> 00:07:32,796
I've seen it a number of times


136
00:07:33,226 --> 00:07:35,816
and it never works
out well in the end.


137
00:07:36,676 --> 00:07:39,186
So let's take for example,
you're making an app


138
00:07:40,146 --> 00:07:43,496
